{
  "texts": [
    "• bidirected, e.g.",
    "A ↔ B: indicates that A is not an ancestor or parent of B, B is not an ancestor or parent of A, and neither are ancestors or parents of a selection variable.",
    "This edge type arises in the presence of latent confounders.",
    "• undirected, e.g.",
    "A -B: A is an ancestor or parent of B or a selection variable and B is an ancestor or parent of A or a selection variable."
  ]
}